description: From Middle English misproud, equivalent to mis- +‎ proud.

adjectives.description: misproud (comparative more misproud, superlative most misproud)

entries.meaning: (archaic) Unduly or unwarrantably proud or vain; wrongly proud; arrogant; haughty. [15th–19th c.]
examples: It is grete scorne to se a mysproude knave / With a clerke that connynge is to prate: / Lete theym go lowse theym, in the devylles date.
